        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 6 at 6:24PM CDT by NWS Bismarck ND</headline>
        <description>At 623 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 6
miles south of Tuttle, or 38 miles northeast of Bismarck, moving
southeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Tuttle and Horsehead Lake.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
